Davus, not having found Pamphilus in the forum, goes, after parting with Byrrhia, to the house of Chremes, to see if what his master told him were true or not. Thus having discovered that the marriage was all mere pretence, he exults, and informs Pamphilus by what signs and conjectures he was led to think so.

The metre is Trochaic Tetrameter Catalectic. v
